    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (84.61) and **Junior Caminero** (78.33) pacing the offense. **Yordan Alvarez** is our clear premier start; despite the lineup status being pending, his elite xwOBA of 0.393 against Hancock\u2019s generous 4.76 xERA makes him an essential anchor. Meanwhile, **Junior Caminero** provides massive value in the utility slot; while the park factor is slightly suppressive, Gil\u2019s bloated 5.74 xERA provides a substantial skill edge that elevates his profile well into our strong start territory. **Christian Yelich** (74.33) also stands out as a high-floor play, benefiting from a favorable platoon advantage and a strong 19% SP skill adjustment against Irvin, whose xERA is the most exploitable among today\u2019s opposing arms.\n\nOur most difficult roster construction choice involved **Josh Smith**, who was benched with a score of 53.82. While his dynamic platoon advantage and a stolen base boost against the slow delivery of Glasnow made him an intriguing option, he was squeezed out by the sheer efficiency of **Caleb Durbin** (62.59) and **Trea Turner** (62.51), both of whom are projected for higher volume in favorable spots. Elsewhere, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (67.85) is an aggressive start; his 14% boost from a dynamic platoon matchup against Mlodzinski makes him our premier speed-focused play for today\u2019s category hunting.\n\nWe are monitoring two specific risks as we approach first pitch. **Chase Meidroth** (55.14) carries a 31% rain risk; while he is currently slotted in, managers should keep a pivot ready if the weather outlook in his venue deteriorates. Additionally, while we are confident in our outfield depth, the decision to bench **Logan O'Hoppe** (35.57) and **Victor Scott II** (35.39) was strictly enforced by our sub-40 floor rule, as both are facing elite arms\u2014Burns and Early, respectively\u2014with xERAs well below 3.00. We will rely on **Dillon Dingler** behind the plate and the high-upside speed dynamics of **Hyeseong Kim** to keep our SB pace steady without compromising our daily efficiency targets.",
